EN: This employee has been appointed as the new project manager.

ZH: 这位雇员被公司评为最佳员工。
EN: This employee has been recognized as the best employee by the company.

ZH: 公司提供给雇员优秀的培训机会。
EN: The company provides excellent training opportunities for employees.

ZH: 这名雇员被解雇了，因为他违反了公司的政策。
EN: This employee was fired because he violated the company's policies.

ZH: 公司每年都会举办一次员工聚会。
EN: The company holds an annual employee gathering.

ZH: 她是公司的一名忠诚雇员，已经服务了10年。
EN: She is a loyal employee of the company and has been serving for 10 years.

ZH: 这位雇员在过去的项目中取得了巨大的成功。
EN: This employee has achieved great success in past projects.

ZH: 我们需要聘请一名有经验的雇员来担任这个职位。
EN: We need to hire an experienced employee for this position.

ZH: 雇员们每月都会收到薪水。
EN: Employees receive their salary every month.

ZH: 新雇员需要接受一段时间的培训才能开始工作。
EN: New employees need to undergo a period of training before starting their work.

ZH: 这个公司非常看重雇员的工作满意度。
EN: This company values employee job satisfaction greatly.

ZH: 这个岗位的雇员需要有很好的沟通能力。
EN: The employees in this position need to have good communication skills.

ZH: 他是公司中最资深的雇员之一。
EN: He is one of the most senior employees in the company.

ZH: 雇员们都参加了一个为期一周的团队建设活动。
EN: The employees all participated in a one-week team building activity.

ZH: 公司每年会给雇员们发放年终奖金。
EN: The company provides annual bonuses to its employees.

ZH: 雇员对于公司文化非常重要。
EN: Employees are crucial to the company culture.

ZH: 雇员们可以享受公司提供的福利待遇。
EN: Employees can enjoy the benefits provided by the company.

ZH: 雇员应该保守公司的秘密。
EN: Employees should keep company secrets confidential.

ZH: 这位雇员表现出色，得到了晋升的机会。
EN: This employee has shown excellent performance and has been given the opportunity for promotion.
